# Changelog - xcesppkg

## 0.0.48

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.21, xcespcli 0.0.28, xcespproc 0.0.35, xcespwdog 0.0.7,
  xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.31 with default-namespace FRR start/stop fix and sudo-based
  frrinit.sh invocation; xcesptest 0.0.29 activate.sh with sudoers rule

## 0.0.47

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.21, xcespcli 0.0.28, xcespproc 0.0.35, xcespwdog 0.0.7,
  xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.29 with dynamic-routing / RtrFrr support and ProcObject::onServerCap()

## 0.0.46

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.21, xcespcli 0.0.28, xcespproc 0.0.34, xcespwdog 0.0.7,
  xcespmap 0.0.7
  - xcespserver: system-mac license auth, docker detection/gating, xcespwdog gen
    config writer, role-based object filtering, server status expansion
  - xcespcli: `show server` command with full capability display
  - xcespproc: `--role` argument, PROC_ROLE in HELLO/HEARTBEAT, SERVER_CAP handler
  - xcespwdog: PROC_CONFIG_FILE support for generated process list
  - xcespmap: PROCESS_ROLE injection and role-adjusted AFFINITY for router/domain nodes

## 0.0.45

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.20, xcespcli 0.0.27, xcespproc 0.0.33, xcespwdog 0.0.6
  with non-blocking xcespproc write path in xcespserver (EPOLLOUT write queue fixes
  TCP listener stall after large CLI_CONFIG_PUT)

## 0.0.44

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.19, xcespcli 0.0.27, xcespproc 0.0.33, xcespwdog 0.0.6
  with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.28: `RtrStaticRoutePObj::remove()` deletes kernel route
  on config removal; `router.validate.py` fix for false "device attribute required"
  validation errors in VLAN address-only merge deltas

## 0.0.43

- Bundles xcespmap 0.0.6 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.27: cross-namespace VLANs now
  use the XCESP interface **instance name** (e.g. `eth1`) in the `interface`
  attr instead of the Linux device name — consistent with same-namespace VLANs;
  xcespmap resolves the instance name to the device name at commit time via the
  new `NEEDS_FULL_CONFIG` mechanism; xcespproc relinked against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.27

## 0.0.42

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.32 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.26: xcespproc relinked
  to include cross-namespace VLAN macvlan support — previous releases had a
  stale xcespproc binary that silently ignored the PARENT_NS INI key

## 0.0.41

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.26: commit-time validation now detects when the
  wrong name (XCESP instance name instead of Linux device name) is used for
  the `interface` attr in cross-namespace VLANs; error lists known device
  names with their instance names as a hint

## 0.0.40

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.25: fix NameError crash in router.validate.py at
  startup and false "device attribute is required" error on cross-namespace
  VLAN commit

## 0.0.39

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.24: fix spurious "device attribute is required"
  validation error when committing a cross-namespace VLAN (interface attr
  inside vlan node was misread as an interface node declaration)

## 0.0.38

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.23: cross-namespace VLAN via macvlan — new
  `parent-router` attr on vlan nodes; when set, a VLAN subinterface is
  created in the named parent router's namespace, a `macvlan mode bridge`
  device is built on top, moved into the target router namespace, and
  configured there; `router.validate.py` check 9 validates the parent-router
  reference at commit time

## 0.0.37

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.26 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.22: interface type attr is
  now an enum (device|loopback|rlink) with TAB/? value completion in CLI

## 0.0.36

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.31 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.21: shutdown default=true
  for interface/vlan; router namespace deleted on shutdown; rlink shutdown
  keeps device (link down)

## 0.0.35

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.30 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.20: VLAN shutdown brings
  link down (device stays), VLAN delete removes device, startup syncs IPs

## 0.0.34

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.29 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.19: physical interfaces
  returned to default network namespace on config deletion

## 0.0.33

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.25, xcespproc 0.0.28 with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.18:
  interface IP cleanup on config deletion; CLI immediate attribute
  name validation

## 0.0.32

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.17: VLAN commit-time validation (interface
  reference and loopback-type checks); vlan.py PARENT_DEVICE fallback fix

## 0.0.31

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.19, xcespcli 0.0.24, xcespproc 0.0.27, xcespwdog 0.0.6
  with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.16: rlink veth pair interface type, syncAddresses()
  failure logging for IPv6 deletion diagnosis, device attr optional for rlink

## 0.0.30

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.15, xcespproc 0.0.26:
  IPv6 address deletion from interfaces now works correctly (fix in
  `IpCmd::parseAddrList()`); `address` and `static-route` instance names
  are now validated as valid IP addresses/prefixes with mandatory mask at commit time

## 0.0.29

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.14, xcespproc 0.0.25:
  new `forwarding` boolean attribute on `router` nodes controls
  `net.ipv4.ip_forward` in the router's Linux network namespace;
  CLI form `[no] forwarding`, default enabled

## 0.0.28

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.13, xcespproc 0.0.24:
  `static-route` no longer exposes a redundant `network` CLI attribute —
  the CIDR prefix is the instance identifier and is now implicit; IPv6
  address deletion from interfaces now works correctly (fix in
  `IpCmd::parseAddrList()`)

## 0.0.27

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.24: case-insensitive CLI keywords with case-preserving
  entity identifiers — instance names such as `RouterA` are accepted and stored
  with their original capitalisation; node-type and instance-name matching in
  navigation and TAB completion are now fully case-insensitive while returning
  the canonical stored form

## 0.0.26

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.19: `ProcClient::handleAck()` fix — `ACK CMD=RESET` no
  longer clears `deployedAttrs_`; fixes double-RESET startup race where both procs
  connecting simultaneously caused a full redeploy on every subsequent commit and
  "registerLink: role already taken" errors in xcespproc-1

## 0.0.25

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.18, xcespproc 0.0.23, xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.12:
  objectsForProc() no longer routes explicitly-affinitied objects to the
  first connected proc when the target proc is absent (fixes spurious
  redeployments on xcespproc-2); xcespproc and xcesp-on-rtr makefile fixes
  ensure plugin library updates trigger automatic relinks

## 0.0.24

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.22 and xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.11:
  unique object names (`router_`, `vrf_`, etc. prefixes) fix spurious
  double-REMOVE on commits; `RtrVrfPObj::remove()` and
  `RtrRouterPObj::remove()` tear down Linux VRF devices and network
  namespaces when config nodes are deleted

## 0.0.23

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.23 and xcespconfig 0.0.7: `delete <type> <instance> [!]`
  node deletion in config mode — removes a named child node and all its
  descendants from the candidate config; `!` suffix required unless in
  create mode; attribute deletion unchanged

## 0.0.22

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.21 rebuilt against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.10:
  `RtrVrfPObj` now deletes the Linux VRF device on shutdown and handles
  table-id changes by deleting and re-creating the device with the correct
  table number

## 0.0.21

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.17: `ProcClient::handleAck()` fix — `ACK CMD=RESET`
  no longer clears `pendingAttrs_`; fixes attr-level diff regression where all
  objects were redeployed on every config commit instead of only changed ones

## 0.0.20

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.22: `CandidateConfig::createNode()` is now idempotent
  — navigating to an existing node in `conf !` mode no longer prints a
  spurious error

## 0.0.19

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.16: attr-level diff in `ProcClient::deployObjects()`
  — on config commit only objects with changed INI attributes are redeployed;
  unchanged objects are silently skipped

## 0.0.18

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.9: `IpCmd::exec()` and `IpCmd::run()` use
  `fork()+exec()` with ambient `CAP_NET_ADMIN`+`CAP_SYS_ADMIN` instead of
  `popen()`/`system()` — fixes VRF and interface creation failing with
  `RTNETLINK answers: Operation not permitted` because file capabilities on
  xcespproc were dropped when exec'ing the unprivileged `ip(8)` binary

## 0.0.17

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.15: `ProcClient::deployObjects()` fixes dual-proc
  deployment race (pending objects now cancelled before ACK can promote them);
  `XCespServer` honours `LOG_CONSOLE_LEVEL` INI key to suppress DEBUG noise

## 0.0.16

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.8: `RtrVrfPObj::applyConfig()` uses
  `IpCmd::exec(cmd, errOut)` to log VRF creation failures at WARNING;
  `monitorVrf()` re-creates missing VRF devices (matching router namespace
  re-creation pattern)

## 0.0.15

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.7: `IpCmd::createNetns()` creates network
  namespaces via `fork()+unshare(CLONE_NEWNET)+mount(MS_BIND)`, bypassing
  `ip netns add`'s `mount --make-shared /run/netns` step that fails for
  non-root processes even with `CAP_SYS_ADMIN`
- `xcesp-activate`: pre-creates `/run/netns` owned by xcesp so xcespproc
  can write namespace bind-files without root privileges

## 0.0.14

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.6: `IpCmd::exec(cmd, output)` overload captures
  stderr; `RtrRouterPObj` now logs the exact `ip netns add` failure message
  at WARNING level when namespace creation or re-creation fails

## 0.0.13

- `cfg/xcespwdog.ini`: enable `[process.3]` — xcespproc instance 2
  (affinity 2); was commented out, causing affinity-2 objects (e.g.
  `router ra`) to fall back to xcespproc-1 instead of running on their
  own dedicated process instance

## 0.0.12

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.14: hook validation now also runs on startup
  config (non-fatal — logs WARNING); invalid configs that pre-date hooks
  are now surfaced at server startup rather than silently persisting

## 0.0.11

- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.5: `router.validate.py` affinity conflict check
- makefile: flatten `*.validate.py` hooks from plugin schema dirs
  (`on-rtr/`, `on-pw/`, `on-xc/`) to top-level `schema/` so xcespserver
  can find them via its single schemaDir

## 0.0.10

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.21: `--whole-archive` fix — `RtrRouter`, `RtrVrf`,
  `RtrInterface`, `RtrVlan`, `RtrStaticRoute` process objects now correctly
  registered at runtime (linker was silently dropping static initialisers)
- Bundles xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.4: remove reserved `attr name` from
  `address.schema` (eliminates WARNING at server startup)

## 0.0.9

- `xcesp-activate`: create `/run/xcesp` with correct ownership/permissions on
  every invocation — `/run` is tmpfs and is cleared on reboot; `RuntimeDirectory=`
  in the systemd unit covers the managed-service path, but manual invocations
  (direct `sudo xcesp-activate`, xcesptest `start.sh`) had no fallback, causing
  xcespserver to fail binding its UDS control socket `/run/xcesp/ctrl.sock`

## 0.0.8

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.13, xcespcli 0.0.21, xcespwdog 0.0.6
- xcespschema 0.0.5: case-insensitive keywords, `_boolean` built-in type,
  `attr name` reserved, schema cross-reference validation (`validateRefs()`)
- xcespconfig 0.0.6: child-ref constraint validation in `validate()`,
  Python hook validation (`validateHooks()`), skip auto-injected `name`
  in validation, IOS bool uses `isUseNoType()` (not `isBoolType()`)
- xcespserver 0.0.13: schema validation now fatal (rejects config on error),
  Python hook validation added to `applyNewConfig()`
- xcespcli 0.0.21: commit pre-validates before sending to server, case-insensitive
  command dispatch, enum canonicalization, IOS bool display fix

## 0.0.7

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.12: startup config loading now uses schema-based
  disambiguation, fixing `shutdown` (single-token bool) being misclassified
  as a child block opener — xcespserver no longer fails to start when the
  config contains bare bool attributes like `shutdown`

## 0.0.6

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.20: `config !` temporarily enables auto-create for
  the config session; `end` restores prior behaviour

## 0.0.5

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.19: `--no-create` is now the default (require `'!'` to
  create nodes); `--create` flag enables auto-creation without `'!'`

## 0.0.4

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.18 with fix for `show running` / `show candidate`
  displaying `shutdown false` instead of `no shutdown` at root navigation level

## 0.0.3

- Bundles xcespcli 0.0.17 with `TerminalParams` CLI flags:
  `-v`/`--verbose <0-5>`, `-l`/`--lines <N>`, `-t`/`--timeout <N>`,
  `--no-create`/`--create`; all map directly to `CliSession::terminalParams()`
  at startup

## 0.0.2

- Bundles xcespschema 0.0.4, xcespserver 0.0.11, xcespcli 0.0.16 with fixes for:
  - Commit rejection when config contains address sub-nodes (xcespserver 0.0.11)
  - `show candidate` displaying `shutdown false` instead of `no shutdown` (xcespcli 0.0.16)
  - `?`/TAB completion and navigation now restricted to valid node types at each
    path depth (root: domain, router only) (xcespcli 0.0.16 + xcespschema 0.0.4)
  - After `discard`, navigation path auto-reset to root if it no longer exists (xcespcli 0.0.16)
  - `TerminalParams` structure added to xcespcli (xcespcli 0.0.16)

## 0.0.1

- Initial release: tarball-based installer for XCESP
- Bundles xcespserver, xcespcli, xcespproc, xcespwdog binaries
- Bundles schema, Python rules (worker + config-to-objects + status-to-global),
  and xcesppy Python client library
- install.sh: creates xcesp system user/group, installs binaries to /usr/bin,
  sets cap_net_admin,cap_sys_admin=ep on xcespproc, installs config templates
  to /var/xcesp/cfg (non-destructive — existing files are not overwritten),
  creates Python venv at /var/xcesp/venv, installs systemd service xcesp.service
